Good question — clarify: AWS auto-provides a DEFAULT key, but a CMK you must
always create yourself. Never auto-created.

What's automatic (zero action needed):

• aws/ebs — default AWS-managed key for EBS, exists in every account automatically

• aws/s3 — default AWS-managed key for S3, exists automatically

• These appear in the dropdown without you doing anything — AWS provisions them at
  account creation, silently, once per account/region

What's NOT automatic (you must create it):

• A Customer Managed Key (CMK) — e.g., alias/globalpayments-s3-key — never
  appears unless you go to KMS console/Terraform and create it explicitly

• If you select "Choose your own key" during EBS/S3 setup and no CMK exists yet,
  the dropdown will be empty — you're expected to create one first, then come
  back and select it

